<TITLE> ECNEC backs projects of Tk3000cr </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 7 (bdnews24.com)  The Executive Committee of the National Economic Council (ECNEC) on Sunday approved 14 projects worth around Tk 3000 crore, with foreign aid accounting for Tk 1396 crore, finance and planning adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam said. The projects were approved at a meet presided over by chief adviser and ECNEC chairman Fakhruddin Ahmed at the National Economic Council conference hall. The approved projects are elevation of the Narayanganj road to four lanes at a cost of Tk 56 crore, construction of three bridges in Khepupara, Mahipur and Hazipur on the Patuakhali-Kuakata road at a cost of Tk 130 crore, construction of a link road from Shirintek to Gabtali bridge at a cost of Tk 39 crore and completion of the 22 kilometres of Patuakhali-Kuakata road at a cost of Tk 57 crore. These projects will be implemented by the Department of Roads and Highways. The other approved projects are construction of the Airport Road-Rokeya Sarani link road at a cost of Tk 33 crore, development of the second urban infrastructure at a cost of Tk149 crore, establishment of the Rangpur University at a cost of Tk 99 crore, purchasing of scientific equipment for public universities at a cost of Tk 227 crore, renovation and repairing of old structures of private universities at a cost of Tk 138 crore, establishment of BAF Shaheen Schools at Shamshernagar, Moulavibazar, Paharkanchanpur and Tangail at a cost of Tk 36 crore, greater Chittagong power distribution project at a cost of Tk 108 crore, pre-payment monitoring project for distribution of power in southern Chittagong at a cost of Tk 137 crore, reinforcement, renovation and augmentation of 33/11 kv sub-station at a cost of Tk 134 crore and development of urban power distribution at a cost of Tk 611 crore. After the Eid holidays, the ECNEC will have another meeting, said the finance adviser. bd
